    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I am on `react-instantsearch-nextjs` v0.3.14 and I am seeing the same issue but without `DynamicWidgets` - instead I am using the hook `useInfiniteHits` to create a custom hits output like this:\r\n\r\n```'use client'\r\nimport { useInfiniteHits } from 'react-instantsearch'\r\n\r\nexport default function InfiniteHits(props: any): JSX.Element {\r\n  const {items, isLastPage, showMore} = useInfiniteHits(props)\r\n  console.log({items})\r\n  \r\n  return (\r\n    <div>\r\n      {items.map((item, index) => (\r\n        <div>\r\n          <a\r\n            href={`/${item.path}`}\r\n            key={index}>\r\n            {item.path}\r\n          </a>\r\n        </div>\r\n      ))}\r\n      {!isLastPage && <button onClick={() => showMore()}>Show More Results</button>}\r\n    </div>\r\n  )\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nand my search provider is set up like this\r\n```\r\n'use client';\r\nimport { liteClient as algoliasearch } from 'algoliasearch/lite';\r\nimport InfiniteHits  from './AlgoliaInfiniteHIts';\r\nimport { InstantSearchNext } from 'react-instantsearch-nextjs';\r\n\r\nconst searchClient = algoliasearch(process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ALGOLIA_APPLICATION_ID || '', process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ALGOLIA_SEARCH_API_KEY || '');\r\n\r\nexport function Search() {\r\n  return (\r\n    <InstantSearchNext \r\n      indexName={process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ALGOLIA_INDEX} \r\n      searchClient={searchClient}\r\n      future={{\r\n        preserveSharedStateOnUnmount: true,\r\n      }}>\r\n      <InfiniteHits/>\r\n    </InstantSearchNext>\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n```\r\nand my local server output looks like this: \r\n```\r\n ⨯ TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading 'state')\r\n    at InfiniteHits (./components/AlgoliaInfiniteHits.tsx:11:113)\r\ndigest: \"1484577836\"\r\n GET /sb 500 in 589ms\r\n ✓ Compiled /favicon.ico in 45ms (588 modules)\r\n GET /favicon.ico 200 in 80ms\r\n```\r\n",
